President Trump welcomed President Santos of Colombia to the White House, reaffirming the partnership between the two nations. They discussed cooperation in addressing drug crimes and the drug epidemic that is affecting both countries. President Trump expressed his willingness to assist Colombia in targeting and eliminating drug trafficking networks, illicit financing, coca cultivation, and cocaine production. He also mentioned the importance of the border wall in stopping drugs and gangs from entering the US. President Santos emphasized the need for collaboration in fighting drug trafficking and reducing coca production. They also discussed the deteriorating situation in Venezuela and the need for a peaceful resolution. Both leaders highlighted the strong economic partnership between the US and Colombia and their commitment to improving the lives of their people.